# Booking workflow — agent reference

This rule is the single source of truth for the **new booking lifecycle** described in `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` (plan) and `docs/NEW FLOW.md` (original spec).

Whenever a task touches **booking state, emails, calendar events, sheet rows, PDF persistence, or the admin dashboard**, start here.

## 1. Status enum (canonical)

Use the string literals below in DB, code, and UI. **Postgres storage:** `TEXT` + `CHECK (status IN (...))` — see `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 **Q1.3** (avoid Postgres `ENUM` churn). Keep a single source (`supabase/functions/_shared/statusMachine.ts` on the server, `ui/src/features/admin/lib/workflow.ts` on the client — keep in sync).

```
PENDING_REVIEW
PENDING_GAF
PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST
PENDING_PET_REQUEST
READY_FOR_CHECKIN
PENDING_SD_REFUND
COMPLETED
CANCELLED
```

> Legacy DB rows have `status = 'booked'` (or `'canceled'`). The migration maps them per **`docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 Q1.1**: check-in **before today (Asia/Manila)** → `COMPLETED`; check-in **today or future** → `PENDING_REVIEW`; canceled rows → `CANCELLED`.

## 2. Allowed transitions

### 2.1 Primary workflow (happy path + cancel)

```
PENDING_REVIEW          → PENDING_GAF | CANCELLED
PENDING_GAF             → PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST | PENDING_PET_REQUEST | READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST → PENDING_PET_REQUEST | READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
PENDING_PET_REQUEST     → READY_FOR_CHECKIN | CANCELLED
READY_FOR_CHECKIN       → PENDING_SD_REFUND | CANCELLED
PENDING_SD_REFUND       → COMPLETED | CANCELLED
COMPLETED               → (terminal)
CANCELLED               → (terminal)
```

### 2.2 Admin-only exceptional transitions

These exist so humans can recover when automation lags or guest data changes late:

```
READY_FOR_CHECKIN       → PENDING_REVIEW   # guest fields edited in admin after ready (see §2.3)
```

**Manual "force advance"** (workflow panel): admins must be able to trigger transitions that would normally be fired by **cron** or the **Gmail listener** when those automations are late or skipped.

Implementation rule: keep **two layers** in `statusMachine.ts`:

1. `canTransition(from, to)` — strict graph for automation + normal admin clicks.
2. `canManualForceTransition(from, to, ctx)` — **small explicit allow-list** of extra edges (e.g. `READY_FOR_CHECKIN → PENDING_SD_REFUND` even before cron, `PENDING_GAF → READY_FOR_CHECKIN` when the approved PDF was uploaded manually, etc.). **Never** accept arbitrary `{ toStatus }` from the client without this second check.

`transition-booking` always calls the orchestrator with `{ manual: true | false }` so the server can tell which validator ran.

The server **must** validate every transition before writing. **Manual advances** and **cron/listener** calls must all go through `workflowOrchestrator.transition()` — never duplicate side-effect logic in callers.

### 2.3 Guest-field edit → revert to review

When `status === READY_FOR_CHECKIN` and an admin saves **material changes** to guest-facing booking fields (dates, guest counts, names, contact, parking/pet flags, uploads, etc.), **set `status` back to `PENDING_REVIEW`** (and update `status_updated_at`). Fan-out (calendar color/title, sheet status column) follows the **new** status.

**Dev-control checkboxes** (save DB, storage, PDF, each email toggle, calendar, sheet) still apply to **every** submit/save — reverting status never bypasses them.

## 3. Side-effect matrix

Each transition fans out a known set of side effects. Implement them inside `_shared/workflowOrchestrator.ts` and call it from the `transition-booking` edge function.

| From → To                                    | DB | Storage             | Calendar            | Sheet | Email(s)                                                                              |
| -------------------------------------------- | -- | ------------------- | ------------------- | ----- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| (guest submit) → PENDING_REVIEW              | ✅ | ✅ (uploads + PDF)  | ❌                  | ❌    | ❌                                                                                    |
| PENDING_REVIEW → PENDING_GAF                 | ✅ | —                   | ✅ yellow, retitle  | ✅   | GAF request (Azure), booking acknowledgement (guest), pet request if pets, parking broadcast if parking |
| PENDING_GAF → PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST        | ✅ | ✅ save approved GAF | ✅ yellow, retitle | ✅   | ❌                                                                                    |
| PENDING_GAF → PENDING_PET_REQUEST            | ✅ | ✅ save approved GAF | ✅ yellow, retitle | ✅   | ❌                                                                                    |
| PENDING_GAF → READY_FOR_CHECKIN              | ✅ | ✅ save approved GAF | ✅ green, retitle  | ✅   | Ready-for-check-in (guest)                                                            |
| PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST → PENDING_PET_REQUEST| ✅ | ✅ parking endorsement | ✅ yellow, retitle | ✅ | ❌                                                                                    |
| PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST → READY_FOR_CHECKIN  | ✅ | ✅ parking endorsement | ✅ green, retitle  | ✅ | Ready-for-check-in (guest)                                                            |
| PENDING_PET_REQUEST → READY_FOR_CHECKIN      | ✅ | ✅ save approved pet PDF | ✅ green, retitle | ✅ | Ready-for-check-in (guest)                                                            |
| READY_FOR_CHECKIN → PENDING_SD_REFUND (cron) | ✅ | —                   | ✅ orange, retitle | ✅   | ❌                                                                                    |
| PENDING_SD_REFUND → COMPLETED                | ✅ | —                   | ✅ blue, retitle   | ✅   | ❌ (or send refund receipt if product wants — confirm)                                |
| any → CANCELLED                              | ✅ | —                   | ✅ purple, retitle | ✅   | ❌ (keep existing cancel behavior)                                                    |

Rules:

- **Never CC the guest** on the GAF-request and pet-request emails to Azure.
- **The guest acknowledgement email** (to guest) is separate and only goes out on `PENDING_REVIEW → PENDING_GAF`.
- The **parking broadcast email** uses BCC to all addresses in `PARKING_OWNER_EMAILS` (comma-separated env var; initial seed list documented in `docs/NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 Q4.1).
- **Parking owner replies** are **manual** in v1 — no Gmail listener for parking threads.

## 4. Calendar color + title map

Implement once in `_shared/calendarService.ts`; the orchestrator passes the target status.

**No square brackets around status labels in production.** Full Google Calendar `summary`:

`{STATUS LABEL} - {pax}pax {nights}night(s) - {guestFacebookName}`

Example: `PENDING REVIEW - 2pax 2nights - Kyle Soriano`

For **test bookings only**, prepend **`[TEST] `** before the status label: `[TEST] PENDING REVIEW - 2pax 2nights - Kyle Soriano`.

| Status                    | `colorId` | `STATUS LABEL` (first segment of `summary`) |
| ------------------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| PENDING_REVIEW            | `11`      | `PENDING REVIEW`                            |
| PENDING_GAF               | `5`       | `PENDING GAF`                               |
| PENDING_PARKING_REQUEST   | `5`       | `PENDING PARKING REQUEST`                   |
| PENDING_PET_REQUEST       | `5`       | `PENDING PET REQUEST`                       |
| READY_FOR_CHECKIN         | `10`      | `READY FOR CHECK-IN`                        |
| PENDING_SD_REFUND         | `6`       | `PENDING SD REFUND`                         |
| COMPLETED                 | `9`       | `COMPLETED`                                 |
| CANCELLED                 | `3`       | `CANCELED`                                  |

Canceled spelling **`CANCELED`** matches today’s cancel-booking UX copy; the **DB `status` literal** remains **`CANCELLED`** (calendar `summary` uses `CANCELED`).

