## 6. Invariants (tests should cover these)

- `submit-form` never calls `sendEmail`, `CalendarService`, or `SheetsService`.
- Only `workflowOrchestrator.transition()` mutates `status` and `status_updated_at` (including manual admin overrides and the `READY_FOR_CHECKIN → PENDING_REVIEW` revert on guest-field edits).
- `get-booked-dates` returns everything where `status <> 'CANCELLED'` (not just `'booked'`).
- Test bookings (`is_test_booking = true`) in **production** never send outbound email, never write Calendar, and never write Sheet — even if an admin checkbox is on (**`NEW_FLOW_PLAN.md` §6.1 Q3.4**).
- Calendar event summary always matches `status → colorId` map; drift means orchestration is broken.
- Gmail listener processes every `message.id` **at most once** (idempotency via `processed_emails` table).

## 7. Don'ts

- Don't re-introduce `?dev=true` / `?testing=true` query params in UI code.
- After the migration ships, **application code** should treat `status` as the **new canonical literals only**. The migration itself may still read legacy `'booked'` / `'canceled'` — that's OK, but delete dead branches once backfill is done.
- Don't put calendar/sheet/email calls inside `DatabaseService`; keep services single-responsibility.
- Don't add side effects inline to transition endpoints — go through the orchestrator so every caller (UI, Gmail listener, cron) behaves identically.
- Don't forget to update `docs/PROJECT.md` and `docs/TODOS.md` per `documentation-maintenance.mdc`.

